MASERU, Lesotho, Feb. 1 (Reuters)—Under orders from Chief Leabua Jonathan, the Prime Minister, policemen to day jailed at least 30 members of the opposition Congress party, including 16 members of the party's executive com mittee.

They joined their leader, Ntsu Mokhehle, who was arrested Friday when Chief Jona than declared a state of emer gency and suspended the Con stitution before the full results were known of the general election held on Tuesday. The opposition appeared to have won a majority.

Members of the opposition said they had appealed to United Nations Secretary Gen eral Thant to step in and end what they asserted was an il legal and unconstitutional coup d'état.